From 998e68843f91a608e02cbc66347f94186ec58304 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergio Prado <sergio.prado@e-labworks.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 07:06:19 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] binman: k3: add PKCS#11/HSM signing support

Allow K3 boot artifacts to be signed using a key stored in an HSM
instead of a plain PEM file on disk, by adding PKCS#11 URI support
to the binman signing pipeline.

Changes:
- binman/btool/openssl.py: add _pkcs11_use_provider() to detect
  whether the OpenSSL pkcs11-provider is available (falling back to
  the legacy engine for OpenSSL < 3.1), _build_key_args() to build
  the correct openssl CLI arguments for PEM or PKCS#11 keys (injecting
  pin-value from PKCS11_PIN env var if set), and _run_cmd_pkcs11() to
  optionally set PKCS11_MODULE_PATH/PKCS11_PROVIDER_MODULE before
  invoking openssl
- binman/etype/x509_cert.py: read optional pkcs11-module entry
  argument and pass it through to all openssl signing calls
- arch/arm/mach-k3/Kconfig: add default "custMpk.pem" to
  SYS_K3_KEY and update help text to document PKCS#11 URI support
- arch/arm/dts/k3-binman.dtsi,
  arch/arm/dts/k3-am625-verdin-wifi-dev-binman.dtsi: replace
  hardcoded keyfile = "custMpk.pem" with CONFIG_SYS_K3_KEY

To sign with an HSM, set CONFIG_SYS_K3_KEY to the PKCS#11 URI and
optionally provide the PIN and module path via PKCS11_PIN,
PKCS11_MODULE_PATH and PKCS11_PROVIDER_MODULE environment variables.

Signed-off-by: Sergio Prado <sergio.prado@e-labworks.com>
